@startuml m1_phase1_v2x_call_flow_sequence
' Research artifact (project-researcher) — Phase 1 V2X call flow: control-plane
' bring-up, data-plane RX (relay path) and TX (ego CAM heartbeat).
' Not an HLD. Module names match m1-phase1-working-env-component.puml and
' m1-phase1-working-env-activity.puml. The "group" frames mark the V2X_Comm
' Phase 1 deliverable boundary: raw datagram in / send API called -> decoded
' PDU handed to ADA / encoded bytes handed to transport.
title Phase 1 V2X Call Flow — bring-up, RX, TX heartbeat (V2X_Comm boundary boxed)

actor "systemd (boot)" as SYSD
box "Bench Node" #DDEBF7
  participant "Scenario Player" as SP
end box
box "Ego vECU (Linux, CabinSky)" #E2EFDA
  participant "V2X_Comm" as V2X
  participant "GnssProvider" as GNSS
  participant "ADA" as ADA
  participant "IVI" as IVI
end box

== Control plane — service bring-up (Phase 1 work STARTS here) ==
SYSD -> V2X : start V2X service on boot (R3)
V2X -> V2X : load externalized config (StationID, endpoint, PC5 service-ID placeholders)
V2X -> GNSS : init provider (sim)
GNSS --> V2X : fix ready (scenario position feed)
V2X -> V2X : open transport adapter (bind/join UDP endpoint)
V2X -> V2X : emit startup log (active provider, fix, transport ready)
note right of V2X
  On hardware this block becomes QMI/AT identify
  + telux cv2x start + Rx/Tx flow setup (R6)
end note

== Data plane RX — B relays C to ego ==
SP -> SP : tick trajectories, build CAM(B) + CPM(B perceives C)
SP -> SP : UPER encode (+ BTP-B envelope, port 2001 / 2009; GN deferred)
SP -> SP : apply impairment (drop / delay / jitter)
SP -> V2X : UDP datagram (UPER facilities payload)
group V2X_Comm Phase 1 deliverable boundary (RX)
  V2X -> V2X : strip UDP encapsulation (transport adapter)
  V2X -> V2X : strip envelope (BTP-B header if used; GN/BTP decode = adapter upgrade path)
  V2X -> V2X : UPER-decode CAM / CPM payload
  alt decode + field validation OK
    V2X -> ADA : decoded V2X PDU (sender ref position, perceived object C, timestamps)
  else decode fails
    V2X -> V2X : log and discard (R4 delivery accounting)
  end
end
ADA -> ADA : log full message parsed into fields (Phase 1 acceptance, R4)
ADA -> IVI : mocked warning event (real data via Phases 2-4 + 6)
IVI -> IVI : render placeholder BEV (real display is Phase 5)
note right of ADA
  Phase 1 work TERMINATES at the decoded PDU
  handed to ADA + the parsed-field log.
  ADA internals and IVI are mocks/stubs here.
end note

== Data plane TX — ego CAM heartbeat ==
loop every 100 ms (10 Hz, R3)
  V2X -> GNSS : read ego position + time
  GNSS --> V2X : position fix (logged at 1 Hz, R6 cloud substitute)
  group V2X_Comm Phase 1 deliverable boundary (TX)
    V2X -> V2X : build full R1 schema with mock object contents
    V2X -> V2X : UPER encode (+ BTP-B envelope)
    V2X -> SP : send encoded packet via transport adapter (UDP datagram)
  end
end
SP -> SP : log ego message parsed into fields (peer-side R4 mirror)

@enduml
